---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const snapshot = [
  { label: "Industry", value: "Life Sciences / Enterprise SaaS" },
  { label: "Role", value: "Director of Product Design" },
  { label: "Scope", value: "8 designers, 3 researchers, cross-functional leadership" },
  { label: "Key Outcomes", value: "50% faster design-to-development, 65% faster task completion" },
];

const decisions = [
  {
    title: "Explainability-first AI interactions",
    text: "We treated AI as decision support, not a black box—designing for clarity, trust, and human oversight in high-stakes workflows.",
  },
  {
    title: "Task-centric workflow structure",
    text: "We moved the experience away from data-heavy screens toward workflow paths that matched how clinical teams actually operate.",
  },
  {
    title: "Component-first platform design",
    text: "We established reusable interaction and UI patterns that reduced fragmentation and improved scalability across product lines.",
  },
];

const outcomes = [
  "Cut design-to-development cycle time by 50% by introducing clearer systems, governance, and execution workflows.",
  "Improved user task completion time by 65% through simplified workflows and stronger information hierarchy.",
  "Created a more consistent enterprise platform foundation through reusable design patterns adopted across product lines.",
  "Enabled AI-informed decision-making with greater transparency, usability, and regulatory confidence.",
];
---

<MainLayout title="AI-Powered Life Sciences Platform | Jorge Obando">
  <section class="case-study-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">SAAMA</p>
        <h1>AI-Powered Life Sciences Platform</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Reframing fragmented clinical research workflows into a scalable enterprise
          platform that improved efficiency, reduced complexity, and made AI support
          more usable in high-stakes environments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="hero-image">
        <img src="/images/SAAMA.jpg" alt="SAAMA platform case study visual" />
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="snapshot-grid" aria-label="Case study snapshot">
      {snapshot.map((item) => (
        <article class="snapshot-card">
          <p class="snapshot-label">{item.label}</p>
          <p class="snapshot-value">{item.value}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The situation</h2>
      <p>
        Clinical trial teams were working across fragmented legacy systems, overloaded
        interfaces, and disconnected workflows. Critical information was spread across
        multiple tools, making routine work slower, harder to manage, and more error-prone.
      </p>
      <p>
        The need was not just a better interface. It was a more coherent platform—one
        that could reduce cognitive load, support regulatory rigor, and make AI useful
        in everyday decision-making.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The challenge</h2>
      <p>
        The challenge was to simplify highly complex, data-dense workflows without
        oversimplifying the reality of clinical research operations. Teams needed faster
        access to information, clearer prioritization, and confidence in system guidance.
      </p>
      <p>
        This required more than usability improvements. It required aligning workflow
        design, information architecture, governance, and platform consistency across
        an enterprise environment with multiple roles and evolving requirements.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p>
        As Director of Product Design, I worked across product strategy, design
        leadership, and systems governance. I guided designers and researchers, aligned
        stakeholders across functions, and helped define a platform direction that could
        scale across modules, teams, and operational contexts.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>How I operated</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid two-up">
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Clarified the real problem</h3>
          <p>
            We reframed the work from “modernizing screens” to improving end-to-end
            clinical workflows and making decision support more usable.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Structured the system</h3>
          <p>
            We used information hierarchy, modular patterns, and design system thinking
            to create a more coherent platform foundation.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Aligned stakeholders</h3>
          <p>
            I worked across product, engineering, and design to build shared
            understanding around priorities, constraints, and platform direction.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Drove execution</h3>
          <p>
            We translated strategy into production-ready systems, reducing rework and
            increasing consistency from design through implementation.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Key decisions</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid one-up">
        {decisions.map((item) => (
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>{item.title}</h3>
            <p>{item.text}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Outcomes</h2>
      <div class="outcomes-card">
        <ul>
          {outcomes.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Reflection</h2>
      <p>
        This work reflects the kind of design leadership I bring to complex environments:
        not just improving interfaces, but building the systems, clarity, and operating
        structure needed to make platforms more usable, scalable, and strategically valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section next-step">
      <h2>Next case study</h2>
      <p>
        Continue to <a href="/case-studies/smb-marketplace-fintech">SMB Marketplace & Fintech Ecosystem</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .case-study-page {
    padding: 2.5rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(320px, 0.9fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: end;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .hero-copy {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #a33a3a;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 4vw, 4.15rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .lead {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #555;
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .hero-image {
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--divider);
    border-radius: 18px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .hero-image img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    min-height: 280px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .snapshot-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .snapshot-card,
  .info-card,
  .outcomes-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--divider);
    border-radius: 16px;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .snapshot-card {
    padding: 1.2rem;
  }

  .snapshot-label {
    margin: 0 0 0.45rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #777;
  }

  .snapshot-value {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #222;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--divider);
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 2.2vw, 2.4rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  }

  .content-section p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  .cards-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .cards-grid.two-up {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .cards-grid.one-up {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .info-card {
    padding: 1.4rem;
  }

  .info-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .info-card p {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .outcomes-card {
    padding: 1.35rem 1.4rem;
  }

  .outcomes-card ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  .outcomes-card li {
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #444;
  }

  .outcomes-card li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .next-step a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.15em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .hero {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .snapshot-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .case-study-page {
      padding: 1.5rem 0 4rem;
    }

    .snapshot-grid,
    .cards-grid.two-up {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 1.02rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
    }

    .hero-image img {
      min-height: 220px;
    }
  }
</style>